      <li>Youth support organisations.</li>
      <li>NDIS-related providers, where appropriate.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

{# Key message #}
<section class="section section--alt" id="key-message" data-animate="fade-up">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Coordination at scale, delivered through our group brands</h2>
    <p>TIC itself does not run lessons. Through our group of driving school brands, we coordinate professional driving instruction across multiple locations. That means one point of contact for your organisation, with the operational backbone of a group sitting behind it.</p>
  </div>
</section>

{# Capabilities #}
<section class="section section--light" id="capabilities">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 data-animate="fade-up">What we can coordinate</h2>
    <ul class="feature-list" data-stagger>
      <li><strong>Centralised coordination.</strong> A single point of contact for your team, not a separate conversation with every instructor.</li>
      <li><strong>Multiple professional instructors</strong> across our group brands.</li>
      <li><strong>Multiple locations</strong>, so your students can be matched to instructors near them.</li>
      <li><strong>Consistent communication</strong>: confirmations, reminders, and follow-up handled on a shared system.</li>
      <li><strong>Invoicing support</strong> that fits how your organisation actually pays for services.</li>
      <li><strong>Student progress reporting</strong>, so you can see how the people you support are going.</li>
      <li><strong>Experience working with funded students</strong>, including the practical realities that come with that.</li>
      <li><strong>High-volume lesson coordination</strong>, suitable for organisations with ongoing demand.</li>
      <li><strong>Alignment with current legislation, QFCC requirements, and child safety procedures</strong>, so the people you support are looked after properly.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

